Abstract: The major implementational problem for reversible jump MCMC is that there is commonly no natural way to choose jump proposals since there is no Euclidean structure to guide our choice. In this paper we will consider a mechanism for guiding the proposal choice by analysis of acceptance probabilities for jumps. Essentially the method involves an approximation for the acceptance probability around certain canonical jumps. We will illustrate the procedure using an example of a reversible jump MCMC application, involving a Bayesian analysis of graphical gaussian models. 
